Returns an integer which based on weather it is negative, zero or positive determines if this node is less than, equal to or greater than the other node.
Null values are considered less than to non null values and comparison between two nulls returns 0.
If this.id.compareTo(other.id) returns 0 (equal) and the class of the value property implements Comparable then the value properties are also compared.

useNaturalOrdering() - Method in class veve.datastructures.trees.NTree
Configures this tree so when traversing the tree the order in which the children of each node is visited corresponds with their natural ordering.
